<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL PLAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Everyday we hear and read of the failures of our schools. I have just witnessed 
a dramatic success. At an inner-city school -- Hobart Elementary -- I saw a 
remarkable performance of "Twelve Angry People." The students almost all have 
accents, Spanish, various Asian languages, but they understand and convey the 
meaning of the speeches. 
</P>
<P>
A gifted and dedicated young teacher, Rafe Esquith, each year produces 
remarkable plays. The audience is as mixed as the performers. I don't know any 
of the students at the school, but I go to the performances each year for the 
pure joy of seeing students excel. How do we lure more dedicated young men and 
women into the teaching profession? 
</P>
<P>
ROSLYN B. SHAPIRO 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
