<P>
'CALLING WILDING WHAT IT IS: EVIL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Will writes: "A society that flinches from the fact of evil will flinch from 
the act of punishment. It should wonder why it does not feel safe." It was 
interesting to note that another column on the same page discussed recent 
incidents of documented police abuse that have gone unpunished. Is police abuse 
less evil? Or did we just flinch! 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL P. OSTRYE 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
