<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
North Carolina forward J.R. Reid says he is awaiting a recommendation from 
Coach Dean Smith, but several National Basketball Assn. coaches say they expect 
Reid to bypass his senior year and make an early entrance into the pros. 
</P>
<P>
"The kid's coming out this year," said an NBA official whose team has a draft 
lottery pick told The News and Observer of Raleigh. "If he doesn't, I'll be 
very, very surprised." 
</P>
<P>
NBA coaches and officials can be fined by the league for talking about college 
underclassmen or assessing their pro potential, and many requested anonymity 
when contacted by the newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
Smith said he had conferred with 11 NBA teams about Reid. But he offered no 
further comment on Reid's future. 
</P>
