<LENGTH>
<P>
122 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: EXIT LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ione Skye, the 18-year-old actress currently starring in "Say Anything," says 
she is thankful she has found a career at such an early age. "Knowing what you 
want to do at a young age is great, and being able to do it while you're in 
your teens is even better. Most kids my age are wondering what they're going to 
do in life, so it's a relief for me. I don't have that problem." Skye is is the 
daughter of 1960s singer Donovan Leitch but dropped his last name while growing 
up in California with her mother after her parents divorced. She decided on the 
name Skye because "that was the (Scottish) island where I was conceived." Her 
first name was selected by her mother and it is the Greek word for purple 
jewel. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
