<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLISH STRIKE CONTINUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WARSAW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 20,000 striking miners demanding more pay held out for a fourth 
successive day on Monday in Poland's four major copper mines. The strikers, who 
say they have halted all copper extraction in Poland -- one of the world's 
largest producers -- said that talks with mine officials have broken down and 
there is no sign of a way out of the impasse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
