<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
2 ARMED TEEN-AGERS ARRESTED IN CAR THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Los Angeles County youths were arrested Monday afternoon on the westbound 
Garden Grove Freeway near Golden West after they allegedly stole a car from the 
owner as he left an east Orange detail shop, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The two 16-year-old males, armed with handguns, approached the owner of a 1986 
IROC Chevrolet Camaro about 2 p.m. Monday as he was leaving Elite Auto 
Detailing at 704 W. Katella Ave. and demanded that he give them his car, said 
Sgt. Tim Brown of the Orange police. 
</P>
<P>
The teens then fled in the car and headed for the westbound Garden Grove 
Freeway. Brown said authorities throughout the area were alerted to the theft. 
</P>
<P>
The two were arrested without incident by a Garden Grove police officer after 
they were stopped along the freeway, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
The youths, who were booked on suspicion of robbery, were being held in Orange 
City Jail pending transfer to juvenile hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
