JACOBSON LEADS SADDLEBACK TO STATE GOLF TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Jacobson won the individual title to help lead Saddleback College to its 
third state golf title in seven years Monday at the Del Rio Golf Course in 
Modesto. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback, which also won state titles in 1983 and 1985 under Coach Bill 
Cunerty, shot a team score of 777 over 36 holes. 
</P>
<P>
Jacobson won the individual title with a 149. He shot 71 in the morning round 
and 78 in the afternoon. Canada finished second at 782 and Canyons third at 
800. Orange Coast finished seventh at 812. 
</P>
<P>
John Gillis of Saddleback shot 150 to finish third. Kevin Goto and Joel Manion 
shot 159 and David Harwood 160, also for Saddleback. 
</P>
