<P>
CUCCIA NAMED TO COACH FOOTBALL AT EL DORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fred Cuccia, varsity football coach at California High School in San Ramon, has 
been named to a similar position at El Dorado High in Placentia. 
</P>
<P>
Cuccia replaces Carl Sweet, who resigned last month after three seasons to 
become the school's athletic director. El Dorado was 6-6 last season under 
Sweet. 
</P>
<P>
Cuccia spent one season at California High, where he led the Grizzlies to a 3-7 
record with three victories in the East Bay Athletic League. 
</P>
<P>
Cuccia also has coached at Glendale Hoover and South Pasadena. He led Hoover to 
an 8-2 record in 1985, but the school forfeited eight victories for using an 
ineligible player. 
</P>
<P>
South Pasadena forfeited six victories in 1987 under Cuccia, also for using an 
ineligible player. Cuccia was among 25 candidates who applied for the position. 
</P>
