</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
151 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noel Harrison will play Professor Henry Higgins -- a role made famous by his 
father, Rex -- in the Opera Pacific production of Lerner and Loewe's "My Fair 
Lady" June 23 to July 2 at the Orange County Performing Arts Center. Patti 
Cohenour, now starring in "The Phantom of the Opera" on Broadway, will play 
Eliza Doolittle, and Stephen Lehew will be Freddy. Other cast members will be 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
The production, created in 1985 for the Michigan Opera Theatre, will be 
directed and choreographed by Lara Teeter. Sets will be by Robert O'Hearn and 
costumes by Charles Caine. Glen Clugston will conduct. 
</P>
<P>
Cohenour was nominated for Tony and Drama Desk awards in 1986 for her 
performance as Rosa Bud in Rupert Holmes' "The Mystery of Edwin Drood." She is 
playing Christine Daae in "Phantom." Lehew has appeared in Michigan Opera 
Theatre productions of "My Fair Lady" and Stephen Sondheim's "Sweeney Todd." 
</P>
</TEXT>
