<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
LAUREL CANYON LOSES ELECTRICITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A minor car accident on Laurel Canyon Boulevard in Studio City triggered a 
power outage that left 4,000 Department of Water and Power customers without 
electricity this morning, some for as long as five hours, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The outage occurred at 11:20 p.m. Monday when a car hit a utility pole on 
Laurel Canyon Boulevard at Berry Drive, DWP spokeswoman Dorothy Jensen said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, whose name was unavailable, suffered only minor injuries, but the 
utility pole hit by the car snapped near the top, bringing down electrical 
wires, officials said. That set off a chain-reaction of stress on the local 
power system. Three circuits that feed electricity to the area were knocked 
out, Jensen said. 
</P>
<P>
Primarily affected were homes and businesses in the Laurel Canyon area between 
Mulholland Boulevard and the Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
