FEDERAL AIDS THERAPY HOT LINE SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government today started a free telephone hot line service to provide the 
public with the latest information on the availability of experimental AIDS 
therapies. 
</P>
<P>
The hot line number is 800-TRIALS-A. It will operate between 9 a.m. and 7 p.m., 
Monday through Friday, the government's National AIDS Program Office announced 
at a news conference. 
</P>
<P>
The institute, part of the National Institutes of Health, coordinates the 
government's AIDS research program. Clinical trials are studies of experimental 
drugs in humans. 
</P>
