GM PLANS SUMMER PLANT SHUTDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Motors Corp. said today that it plans to shut down some of its assembly 
plants for a month or longer this summer to help reduce inventories and provide 
time for plant retooling. 
</P>
<P>
There has been speculation that GM, Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. would 
have longer-than-normal changeover times because of slow sales and ambitious 
production during the first three months of the year. 
</P>
<P>
GM spokeswoman Marcia McGee said today that the company's plant in Flint, 
Mich., will be closed between June 13 and Aug. 7 and that plants in Wentzville, 
Mo., and Orion Township in Oakland County will shut down for about a month each 
during June and July. 
</P>
<P>
She called the shutdown time normal. 
</P>
