<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
ITT OKS 11% STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BAL HARBOUR, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Directors of ITT Corp. today approved the adoption of an employee stock 
ownership plan that, together with an existing plan, will give employees an 11% 
stake in the company, ITT said. 
</P>
<P>
The company, at its annual meeting here, said the ESOP will hold $700 million 
of newly issued convertible preferred stock, equal to about 7% of the company's 
voting shares. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the ESOP will be used to buy back about 12 million common or 
common-equivalent shares, so that the stake held by current stockholders is not 
diluted, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
