P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
DEFENSE DEPT. CUTS AIRCRAFT PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Defense Department said today it wants to see the V-22 Osprey aircraft 
project shut down "in an orderly manner" but has no intention of providing any 
more federal funds to the two contractors involved. 
</P>
<P>
Reiterating Friday's announcement that no more money would be forthcoming for 
Bell Helicopter Textron Inc. and the Boeing Helicopter Co. for the project, the 
department said the political outcry after Defense Secretary Dick Cheney's 
decision to terminate the program was "not unexpected." 
</P>
