IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
DERBY CHIEF TREATED FOR ALCOHOLISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOUISVILLE, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three days after the running of the 115th Kentucky Derby, the president of 
Churchill Downs today checked into a 28-day treatment program for alcohol 
abuse, the track announced. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas H. Meeker was expected to return to his post immediately upon completing 
the program, said Warner L. Jones Jr., chairman of the board of Churchill 
Downs. 
</P>
<P>
Karl Schmidt, a spokesman for the track, issued a tersely written three 
paragraph statement saying that Meeker had entered the program. Schmidt said he 
could not reveal which treatment program Meeker had checked into or provide any 
additional comment. 
</P>
